Practical Task 4: Short Paragraph Explaining How ChatGPT Uses NLP
ChatGPT uses Natural Language Processing (NLP) to understand, interpret, and generate human language. It analyzes the words, grammar, and context of a user's message to understand the intended meaning. Using machine learning and deep learning models trained on large amounts of text, ChatGPT predicts the most appropriate response. This enables it to answer questions, hold conversations, translate languages, summarize text, and assist with many language-related tasks.

